Comment:
Ironically before Teen Titans, We had the Musicians of the Introduction song (Ami & Yumi) Whom had their very own animated tv series called "HiHi Puffy Ami Yumi" a few months before Teen Titans first made their debut back in 2003-2006 ish, I think that In my opinion Cartoon Network has been experimenting since day one, There was (Adult Swim) (Toonami) & one of my personal favorite "Cartoon Cartoons" which featured a few fan favorites such as "A Pup Named Scooby Doo" & Tom & Jerry Kids, formally known as "Hanna-Barbera" which had gained the most control over Cartoon Network.

"Cartoon Cartoons" was a small set of mixed cartoons that gave writers & animators a chance to push some of their cartoons into what is known as cartoon network. . Featured some of the most bizarre cartoons such as "Billy & Mandy" "Cow & Chicken" & "Dexters Lab" even "Codename Kids Next Door" There were many others too, along side small shows that didn't exactly make it to the block. (Mina & the Count) Even in Recent past years Cartoon Network was experimenting with Reality shows such as "Dude What would happen" which nearly killed Cartoon Networks Ratings... CN also Tried a Family Movie Night, which did not last very long.

Shows come & shows go.. Heck I remember my most favorite Show on cartoon network that was around the same generation of the original Samurai Jack, formally called (Megas XLR) It was like the & I mean THE BEST Western Anime of all time, to this day, It was like THE Ben 10 of its time. One of the Best.

The Experiments go on to this day, The reason why I bring all this up is because by the end of the day, The Channel is called (Cartoon Network) & some realized this more than others, So they pulled Teen Titans from underneath us. It was considered to be a Super Hero Anime, (Some viewers) could easily take the series as Edgy, Rather Mature for younger audiences, & somewhat hard to follow or understand since there was a plot (Beginning, Middle, End)

The last thing we got to see was its Movie "Trouble in Tokyo", Lets face it Cartoon Network does not do well in the movie Theaters before Teen Titans GO! to the movies, we had the Power Puff girls the movie, which barely made even in the box office. Cartoon Network knew that some of their shows they were airing were rather to risque for younger viewers, Some episodes even got Banned from Cartoon Network Such as the (Rude Removal) "Dexters Lab"

So In my Opinion We have Teen Titans GO! because its a Cartoon, they followed the idea of the original But gave it very similar art style that we saw in (HiHi Puffy Ami Yumi) Which did came out before Teen Titans, In fact They were the ones who promoted Teen Titans overall since they sang the introduction song in both shows, & promoted it in mid season.

Cartoon Network now has very high standards for what they run on they want to remain as Cartoon orientated as much as possible, since they learned from past mistakes, & even in some cases flaws as well. . .

Im not mister know it all. But I been following Cartoon Network since Mid to late 90s (I even Remember) Sheep in the Big City, & Mike Lu & Og

The experiments go on to this very day,

We had the hit series that taught us how to be funny in the kitchen "Chowder"

(Later down the ladder we had) a Show that made the great out doors fun such as Summer Vacation or Summer Camp, (Camp Lazlo)

Then shortly we were diving into the deep blue see, with captain k'nuckles in "The Marvelous Misadventures of Flapjack"

to those who are reading will claim that this has nothing to do with anything, but you'll notice a pattern, There was a Theme, There was some sort of activity which involved getting outside or doing something productive, Each show was different in their own way, but also had very similar tastes.

If I can recall in recent years, Id say Uncle Grandpa would be next, teaching kids to respect their elders & that the elderly folk can be very entertaining.

Another would be the amazing world of gumball which teaches all viewers young or Old. (Family Morals & conflict in a funny yet witty cartoon setting)

So when you say Teen Titans GO! is awfull & that the animation is horrible, or "I miss the original" " I prefer the Original" you are entitled to you're opinion,

But I want you to look back at whats said, maybe you'll understand how cartoon network network functions. 
by the end of the day, Its still a cartoon company, that promote cartoons. Which should remain like so.

Comment:
Honestly, I've never really watched a full episode of Teen Titans Go.  But I loved the original 2003 series.  I just got back from watching this film, and, in all honesty, I enjoyed it a lot.  There were a few jokes and stupid parts that were a bit hard to get through, but overall, I think it was a legitimately solid film.  It must be taken as a parody/comedy film first and foremost, this is not the original Teen Titans series.  Keep that in mind, and I think that the film was actually pretty enjoyable most of the time.  I mostly went out of loyalty to the original series, and chasing a rumor that if this movie did well, then the original might get a 6th season.  But overall, what I got was better than what I was expecting.  I could legitimately still see the original Titan's characters shining through, even in the more dramatic moments of the film (though they do exaggerate a few of the character quirks a bit too much).  The original voice actors are still there, and there is still a part of me that loves hearing Robin shout "Titans Go!," or hearing Beast Boy crack bad jokes, hearing Cyborg shout "Boo Ya!," Raven saying her magical catchphrase, and hearing Starfire's slightly mangled English.

One thing I wish would've been different, but am also kind of happy about is that Ron Perlman didn't voice Slade.  On the one hand, Ron Perlman's version of Slade is one of the best, if not the best, villains I've ever seen.  But then again, that mostly comes because of how sinister Perlman portrayed him, and honestly, I don't think that would've worked in this movie.  So I didn't mind so much that Slade was voiced by a different voice actor.  

In my opinion, the climax of the film was actually kinda epic too.  The music was nice and the jokes (aside from few large groaners) were nice as well)

But the thing at the end (those who have seen it will know what I'm talking about) pretty much makes it worth it to see the film, just for that.  

All in all, I think this movie is worth seeing, even if you didn't like Teen Titans Go that much, I hope that it does well and that because of that, the original Teen Titans gets a 6th series.

In all honestly, this is closer to what these superhero movies should be like. By that I mean, rather than making shit live action ones for teenagers and "adults" who are kids/teenagers mentally, at least when it comes to the shit they watch, why not make more like this, where it has a clear target demographic that it's actively trying to please? Infinitely better than trying to convince people in their early mid 20s+ that comic book movies are serious business for adults. 
First superhero movie trailer I've seen that actually looks like a fun movie that can make you smile, instead of Chris Evans and Chris Hemsworth punching robots and other faceless hordes of whatever the designer whipped up in 20 minutes. And for a perfect contrast, watch this trailer back-to-back with that embarrassing "Fuck Batman" Titans movie trailer that just came out. 
God, I can't wait for it all to die. If you want to help: DON'T PAY FOR THE NEXT SHITTY LIVE ACTION MARVEL OR DC MOVIE, and pay for a ticket to something that looks unique and interesting, or just save your fucking $8 or however much.

So that's what triggered the tale thus the story ends with the best soldier THANOS in infinity war. As quoted above, the for instance, from that example a pattern was forge that governs the story theme which later became the MCU. Title: Teen Titans GO! To The Movies - Official Trailer 1 [HD]
Comment:
I feel like this movie is just a way for DC to end Teen Titans GO with a "bang". I find a lot of things odd about this movie, other than the fact that this is a movie that is being made and will be released as a full length feature film. One is that they have Will Arnett as Deathstroke (I mean "Slade"), when Batman is in this movie and was used as a running gag occasionally in the show and Will Arnett is famous for playing Batman in the Lego Movie Universe. Secondly, I find it odd that they can name-drop Deadpool 5 times but they can't call Slade Deathstroke. I don't think the name Deathstroke is more inappropriate Deadpool, considering Deadpool has a franchise of rated R movies that the main demographic of this show/"movie" should watch/know, unless they think he's Spider-Man. I'm not saying this is gonna be the worst movie of all time, but maybe the worst of this year depending on how Aquaman does. Also it releases the day before the 1 year anniversary of The Emoji Movie, so it really doesn't have the opening date going for it either. It will most likely end up as an average modern DC movie.




And yes, I am more of a Marvel fanboy in case you were wondering. Don't @ me!

Title: Teen Titans GO! To The Movies - Official Trailer 1 [HD]
Comment:
I admit that i have quite a dislike for the show Teen Titans Go, and i highly prefer the original Teen Titans. But there have been a few episodes throughout the series that i found funny and enjoyable. But the ones i hate so much is when the characters act so unlikable and mean-spirited, cheesy humor like large amount of toilet humor, and terrible episode plots. I hate episodes like Serious Business, The Return of Slade, Smile Bones, True Meaning of Christmas, Boys vs Girls, Waffles, Best Robin, and hot Garbage.

But from the view of this trailer, it doesn't look too bad. And this Slade is nowhere near as good as the original Slade, but his villainy quality seems passable for a show like Teen Titans Go. Ironically, i wish he kept his personality from the original. And as much as i hate Robin in most of the episodes of the show, it still is pretty sad that he gets treated poorly because of his role as a sidekick.

If this movie manages to be entertaining, funny, full of tons of action, and has a really good and inspiring moral at the end, i won't consider it a really terrible movie.

If it's not for the fans of the original show then why do the Titans have a similar design from the original show and have the same voice actors.
